info.name: Facial colliculus
info.description: The facial colliculus is a surface bump or elevation on either side of the midline in the floor of the fourth ventricle in the caudal pons.  It is formed by the facial motor nerve fibers passing over the abducens nucleus. It is part of the median eminence located medial to the sulcus limitans in the floor of the fourth ventricle
